---
layout: base
title: Editorial calendar
description: Every article we've published, laid out by date — what ran when, at a glance.
permalink: /editorial-calendar/
---
{# Every published article. Rendered as JSON below; the client builds
   the month-by-month calendar grid (cross-month weekday alignment is
   ugly to do in Nunjucks). #}
{% set allItems = collections.allContent %}

<main class="container ed-cal" data-pagefind-ignore>

  <header class="ed-cal__header">
    <p class="ed-cal__kicker">Reader tools</p>
    <h1 class="ed-cal__title">Editorial calendar</h1>
    <p class="ed-cal__lede">
      What we&rsquo;ve published, day by day. A live record of how the
      paper has filled out over time &mdash; useful for editors planning
      cadence and for readers tracking back to a date.
    </p>
  </header>

  {# Build the month list in JS via the data the template emits below.
     Server-rendering the calendar grids via Nunjucks loops gets gnarly
     fast (cross-month spillover, weekday alignment), so we emit the
     article list as JSON and let a tiny client renderer draw the grid.
     This page is reader-tools, not a primary read surface, so JS-only
     is acceptable. #}
  <div id="ed-cal-mount" class="ed-cal__mount" aria-live="polite">
    <p class="ed-cal__loading">Loading calendar&hellip;</p>
  </div>

  <script id="ed-cal-data" type="application/json">
    [
    {%- set _items = [] -%}
    {%- for item in allItems -%}
      {%- if loop.index0 > 0 -%},{%- endif -%}
      {
        "url": {{ item.url | dump | safe }},
        "title": {{ item.data.title | dump | safe }},
        "section": {{ (item.data.section or "") | dump | safe }},
        "author": {{ (item.data.authorName or "") | dump | safe }},
        "date": {{ (item.date | htmlDateString) | dump | safe }}
      }
    {%- endfor -%}
    ]
  </script>

  <noscript>
    <p class="ed-cal__noscript">
      The calendar grid needs JavaScript. The full article list is
      available without JavaScript at <a href="/archives/">/archives/</a>.
    </p>
  </noscript>

</main>

<script src="/assets/js/editorial-calendar.js?v={{ buildTime }}" defer></script>
